Chenopodium album

   [17797.jpg]
   Authority L.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Caryophyllidae:Caryophyllales:Chenopodiaceae
   Synonyms Chenopodium album ssp. album L.
   Common names lamb's-quarters, pigweed, fat hen, frost blite, mutton
   tops, dirtweed, lamb's quarters, dirty dick, midden myles, baconweed,
   cenizo blanco, weißer gänsefuß, svinmålla, mjölmålla, vitmålla,
   meldestokk, hvidmelet gåsefod, jauhosavikka, hélunjóli
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 17797

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A herb. USES Cultivated for its leaves and seeds.
   The seeds are ground into flour and the leaves are eaten as green
   vegetables. Both the leaves and seed are rich in iron, calcium, and
   vitamins B and C. Parts of the plant produce a reddish-golden dye and
   the plant is also used as fodder. GROWING PERIOD Annual. COMMON
   NAMES Fat hen, Lamb's-quarters, White goosefoot, Lambsquarter.
   FURTHER INF The plant is producing poisons.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Kernick M 1961 pp 183
   Duke J 1975 pp 11 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 32 [USE, FER]
   Jansen P 1991 pp 179
   Duke J 1979 pp 98 [RAIN, TEMP, PH]

